steps.description:
Adding ability to declare multiple "test cases" within a Rego `test_` rule, which is then individually reported (grouped under their parent rule) when running `opa test`. E.g.:

```rego
package example_test

test_concat[note] if {
	some note, tc in {
		"empty + empty": {
			"a": [],
			"b":
```yaml
test_method_not_allowed[input.method] {
    not allow with input.method as ["POST", "DELETE", "PUT", "PATCH"]
}
```

